    • Class de.jannlab.core.CellArray extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -322002318603819740L

      • Serialized Fields

        • cellslbd

          int cellslbd
          The lower bound of the cell range specified by the CellArray.

        • cellsubd

          int cellsubd
          The upper bound of the cell range specified by the CellArray.

        • cellsnum

          int cellsnum
          The number of cells in the range specified by the CellArray.

        • indeg

          int indeg
          The input degree of all cells contained by the layer. This field is redundant to predsnum but is used while the generation process to verify result.

        • outdeg

          int outdeg
          The output degree of all cells contained by the layer. This field is redundant to succsnum but is used while the generation process to verify result.

        • predslbd

          int predslbd
          The lower bound of the links from all predecessors of the cells in the CellArray.

        • predsubd

          int predsubd
          The upper bound of the links from all predecessors of the cells in the CellArray.

        • predsnum

          int predsnum
          The number of links from all predecessors of the cells in the CellArray.

        • predswnum

          int predswnum
          The number of weights of all predecessor links.

        • succslbd

          int succslbd
          The lower bound of the links to all successors of the cells in the CellArray.

        • succsubd

          int succsubd
          The upper bound of the links to all successors of the cells in the CellArray.

        • succsnum

          int succsnum
          The number of links to all successors of the cells in the CellArray.

        • succswnum

          int succswnum
          The number of weights of all successor links.

        • layer

          int layer
          Refers the parent layer.

        • compidx

          int compidx
          Defines the computation-point-of-time in the corresponding layer. If the value is -1 this indicates that the CellArray contains non-computing cells.

        • ilctag

          int ilctag
          This tag can be one of ILC_IN, ILC_OUT or ILC_BOTH. It indicates the "connective-type" of the cells. This allows to define input, output and "hidden" cells per layer.

        • celltype

          CellType celltype
          The CellType gives the functional specification (i.e. the integration and activation function) of the cells in this CellArray.
          See Also:
          CellType

      serialVersionUID:
      52359162370719687L

      • Serialized Fields

        • cellslbd

          int cellslbd
          Gives the lower bound of the cells contained by this layer.

        • cellsubd

          int cellsubd
          Gives the upper bound of the cells contained by this layer.

        • cellsnum

          int cellsnum
          Gives the number of the cells contained by this layer.

        • arrayslbd

          int arrayslbd
          Gives the lower bound of the arrays contained by this layer.

        • arraysubd

          int arraysubd
          Gives the upper bound of the arrays contained by this layer.

        • arraysnum

          int arraysnum
          Gives the number of the arrays contained by this layer.

        • complbds

          int[] complbds
          Gives the lower bounds of the packages of computational independent arrays. Arrays with the same computation index are computed at the same time.

        • compubds

          int[] compubds
          Gives the uppder bounds of the packages of computational independent arrays. Arrays with the same computation index are computed at the same time.

        • compwidth

          int compwidth
          Gives the number of the packages of computational independent arrays.

        • indeg

          int indeg
          Gives the degree of incoming connections to all cells contained by all array in this layer.

        • outdeg

          int outdeg
          Gives the degree of outgoing connections of all cells contained by all array in this layer.

        • tag

          int tag
          Gives the tag of the layer, which contains information of its computational behavior.

    • Class de.jannlab.core.NetBase extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      4485482287977886674L

      • Serialized Fields

        • structure

          NetStructure structure
          Provides the network structure of this network instance.
          See Also:
          NetStructure

        • data

          NetData data
          Provides the network data of this network instance.

        • frameidx

          int frameidx
          Gives the current frameidx of the network. This can be considered as an inner state during the computation process.

        • outputport

          ReadPort outputport
          Provides a read port to the output data of this network. This port targets to the range of output cells in the output buffer using the current frameidx.

        • inputport

          WritePort inputport
          Provides a write port to the input data of this network. This port targets to the range of input cells in the output buffer using the current frameidx.

        • targetport

          WritePort targetport
          Provides a write port to the target data of this network (necessary to compute the error). This port targets to the range of output cells the gradinput buffer.

    • Class de.jannlab.core.NetData extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      9138637243730569419L

      • Serialized Fields

        • input

          double[][] input
          provides the input buffer. the results of the forward integrations are stored here.

        • output

          double[][] output
          provides the output buffer. the results of the forward activations and also the network input are stored here.

        • gradinput

          double[][] gradinput
          provides the grad. input buffer. the results of the backward integrations and also the network error are stored here.

        • gradoutput

          double[][] gradoutput
          provides the grad. output buffer. the results of the activation deviations and also the "back-flowing" error are stored here.

        • framewidth

          int framewidth
          determines the frame width, which is the first dimension of the data buffers. MLPs or trained RNNs only need a frame width of 1. Online offline computing RNNs or online computing RNNs during training need a frame width > 1.

        • weights

          double[] weights
          provides the vector of weigts. note that the first value of the vector is generally 1.0. this is founded in some runtime peformance improvements concerning non weighted links.

        • weightsnum

          int weightsnum
          Gives the number of weights exclusive the constant 1.0 weight.

        • asgns

          int[] asgns
          Stores the indices to the cells used for constant value assignments.

        • asgnsv

          double[] asgnsv
          Stores the constant values assignments corresponding to the indices given in asgns.

    • Class de.jannlab.core.NetStructure extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -4202226869611119404L

      • Serialized Fields

        • cellsnum

          int cellsnum
          Gives the complete number of cells.

        • valcellsnum

          int valcellsnum
          Gives only the number of values cells.

        • comcellsnum

          int comcellsnum
          Gives the number computing cells (non-value).

        • incellslbd

          int incellslbd
          Gives the lower bound of the range of input cells.

        • incellsubd

          int incellsubd
          Gives the upper bound of the range of input cells.

        • incellsnum

          int incellsnum
          Gives the number of input cells.

        • outcellsnum

          int outcellsnum
          Gives the number of output cells.

        • outcellslbd

          int outcellslbd
          Gives lower bound of the range of output cells.

        • outcellsubd

          int outcellsubd
          Gives the upper bound of the range of output cells.

        • layers

          Layer[] layers
          provides the array of layers.

        • layersnum

          int layersnum
          gives the number of layers.

        • recurrent

          boolean recurrent
          determines whether the network has recurrent connections or not.

        • offline

          boolean offline
          determines whether the network computes "offline" or "online".

        • bidirectional

          boolean bidirectional
          determines whether the network is bidirectional, which a special form of offline computing networks.

        • inputlayer

          int inputlayer
          gives the index of the input layer.

        • outputlayer

          int outputlayer
          gives the index of the output layer.

        • arrays

          CellArray[] arrays
          provides all CellArray instances of the networks.

        • arraysnum

          int arraysnum
          gives the number of cellarrays.

        • links

          int[] links
          provides all links of the network in dst major order. this links are used in forward computation.

        • linksrev

          int[] linksrev
          provides all links of the network in src major order, where this src and dst values are additionally swapped. so we can say that linksrev contains the inverted links.

        • linksnum

          int linksnum
          gives the number of links in this network.

        • weightsnum

          int weightsnum
          Gives the number of weights exclusive the constant 1.0 weight. (redundant to NetData.weightsnum). The number of weights can be less than the number of links.
